## The Real Question

Cometly is solid for paid-ad attribution and CAPI enrichment. You're here because you need attribution across all channels—not just Meta and Google Ads—or you want transparent pricing and model inspection.

### Quick Answer

**Need all-channel attribution (organic + email + paid)?** Cometly only sees ads.
→ **mbuzz** — 8 models, all channels, server-side tracking, $29-299/mo

**Need LTV attribution?** Cometly attributes to first purchase only.
→ **mbuzz** — tracks recurring revenue back to acquisition source

**Want transparent pricing + custom models?** Cometly requires a demo call.
→ **mbuzz** — published pricing, custom rule editor on all plans

**Want Shopify-native simplicity?** Cometly isn't Shopify-specific.
→ **Triple Whale** — $129-279/mo, Shopify app

**Need B2B revenue attribution?** Cometly doesn't understand sales cycles.
→ **mbuzz** for model flexibility, **HockeyStack** for all-in-one, **Dreamdata** for journey viz

**Want ML-powered enterprise attribution?** Cometly is rule-based.
→ **Northbeam** — $400+/mo, ML fractional

### The Uncomfortable Truth

Cometly is genuinely good at what it does—improving ad platform signal quality and CAPI match rates. If your business is 90% paid ads and you want to optimize Meta/Google, Cometly may actually be the right tool. This guide is for teams who need to see the full picture beyond paid ads.

The real limitation: Cometly answers "how do I optimize my ad platforms?" but can't answer "which channels actually drive revenue?" If organic search brings 40% of your customers and email drives 25% of repeat revenue, Cometly doesn't see any of that.

*If paid ads are your entire world and CAPI enrichment is your top priority, Cometly delivers. Read on if you need more.*

### Common Reasons to Switch

| Limitation | Impact |
|------------|--------|
| **Paid-ads only** | No attribution for organic, email, referral, or lifecycle |
| **Opaque pricing** | Must schedule demo—no published pricing |
| **No custom models** | 4 basic models, no custom logic |
| **No incrementality testing** | Can't validate if attribution is accurate |
| **Client-side tracking** | Misses events blocked by ad blockers |

If any of these resonate, here are your best options.

